    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Some of the items stored in the db are nicely separable (eg: deposits, merkle tree, etc).\r\nI think there may be some trickiness w/ blocks/states since there is more overlap eg setChainHeadRoots deals with both blocks and states.\r\n\r\nWe're also storing some \"well known\" roots, which we transparently fetch in eg: getFinalizedState, which does a Key -> root lookup, then root -> state lookup. My thought was that eventually we would have a wrapper caching layer that would store/fetch the \"well known\" things from memory and avoid the double-lookup.\r\n\r\nThis is all just fyi.",
